### 2.3 Agent-Plugin Control Bus

**Current State**: Agents compute positions/velocities but can't directly modulate plugin parameters.

**Solution**: Bidirectional control bus via `context.agent_controls`:

```python
# Agent code (agents/physics.py)
def step(self, context):
    # Compute new position
    context.agent_controls[f"{self.id}.param_x"] = self.position.x
    context.agent_controls[f"{self.id}.param_y"] = self.velocity.y
    
# Plugin code (plugins/depth_motion_transfer.py)
def process(self, input_texture, params, context):
    # Read agent controls
    param_x = context.agent_controls.get(f"agent_{self.id}.param_x", params["x"])
    param_y = context.agent_controls.get(f"agent_{self.id}.param_y", params["y"])
    
    # Use agent-modulated values
    displacement = compute_displacement(input_texture, param_x, param_y)
    return displaced_texture
```

**Wiring Points:**
1. `agents/bridge.py` aggregates all agent controls into `context.agent_controls` dict
2. Plugins read from `context.agent_controls` with fallback to static params
3. UI can display agent→plugin mappings in real-time

**Implementation Spec**: `docs/specs/P8-I8_agent_plugin_bus.md`

